result.execSummary:
The defendant Rydall J. Gentry was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Failure to Support Child (120 Days+), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.22(2).
  • Failure to Support Child (120 Days+), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.22(2).
  • Failure to Support Child (120 Days+), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.22(2).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Case called at 10:00 am [Clerk SH]
[Reserve Judge Neal Nettesheim presiding for BrIV]
Defendant Rydall J. Gentry in court with Attorney Yelena Olegovna Zarwell. ADA Monica J. Hall appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Court examines the Defendant as to rights, understanding & intent. Mr. Gentry waives his right to Preliminary Hearing; the Court accepts this waiver and binds him over for Arraignment.
State files information; Arraignment:--service of Information admitted, reading waived

Constitutional rights given; plea of "No Contest" entered on Counts #1, #2 & #3; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance verified; Court finds the plea has been entered freely, voluntarily, intelligently and accepts the plea, finds Defendant guilty, and orders JOC entered.
On Motion of the State, the Court reads-in and dismisses Counts #4 - #8
ADA Hall submits victim impact statement

On Counts #1, #2 & #3, the Court withholds sentence, places Defendant on Probation for 5 years, each count, concurret, with conditions:
--AODA Assessment & Follow Through with any recommended treatment, per Agent
--To undergo any other assessment, treatment or counseling as required per Agent
--To maintain employment
--Comply with ALL family court orders regarding child support
--Make all child support payment on time
--Make all payments on arrearages according to any child support orders
--Within 5 days of sentencing (or if confined, within 5 business days of release from custody), defendant shall report to the child support agency - Jefferson County Courthouse, 311 S. Center Ave. Jefferson Rm219, to complete a case management meeting
--Advise child support office of any employment or address change within 48 hours of such a change
--To pay $750 DNA Surcharge ($250 each count)
--To submit DNA Sample upon demand
--Not leave the State of Wisconsin without court approval
--All payments towards child support and arrearages are to be paid through: WISCONSIN SUPPORT COLLECTION TRUST FUND, PO Box 74200, Milwaukee WI 53274-0200 not through DOC
Court does not impose costs

Days credit for time already served: 0 days
Felony Firearm/Voting Prohibitions Warnings Form Given
Recess: 10:32 am
Status conference on December 12, 2014 at 09:30 am.
Pre-trial conference on November 19, 2014 at 03:20 pm.
